            "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nThis should consider errorformat to be useful with more than a few compilers.\r\nI am not sure how a new spec would change things. Right now I would go for something like this:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nfunction get_loc()\r\n    local elems = vim.fn.getqflist {\r\n        efm = vim.o.errorformat,\r\n        lines = {vim.api.nvim_get_current_line()}\r\n    }.items\r\n\r\n    if #elems < 1 then\r\n        return false\r\n    else\r\n        return true, elems[1].bufnr, elems[1].lnum, elems[1].col\r\n    end\r\nend\r\n\r\nfunction jump(buffer, line, col)\r\n    vim.api.nvim_win_set_buf(0, buffer)\r\n    vim.api.nvim_win_set_cursor(0, {line, col})\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.keymap.set(\"n\", \"gF\", function()\r\n    local ok, bufr, line, col = get_loc()\r\n    if ok then\r\n        jump(bufr, line, col)\r\n    end\r\nend)\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote: getqflist automatically bind the filename to a new buffer number.",
